## Decisions made
- **Render OUTSIDE the DB transaction — design fix the memory gate surfaced.**
  First cut wrapped the whole render in tenantWorker's single withTenant() tx
  (like imports VALIDATE). The 40-card gate exposed it: holding a Prisma
  interactive tx across a multi-second Chromium render blows the 5s tx timeout
  ("Transaction already closed… 72100 ms passed"). Refactored renderCard to own
  its txns like imports COMMIT: (1) SHORT tx read-data + flip GENERATING, (2) NO
  tx render + store, (3) SHORT tx flip GENERATED + audit. Processor dropped
  tenantWorker (kept a schoolId/reportCardId guard). **Lesson: never hold a DB
  tx across a seconds-long, externally-bounded operation.**
- **Dropped `--single-process` / `--no-zygote`** — they crash page.pdf() with an
  empty-message protocol error (Windows; known cross-platform PDF footgun). Kept
  `--no-sandbox --disable-setuid-sandbox --disable-dev-shm-usage --disable-gpu`.
  Memory bounded by page-recycle + concurrency-1, not by those flags.
- **esc() is the single XSS boundary** — hand-rolled template, every
  user-controlled field through esc(); a unit test runs `<script>` through every
  field. esc is deliberately NOT idempotent (re-escapes `&`); documented+tested.
- **Deterministic storage path** = idempotent re-render (overwrite in place).
  artifactUrl stores the PATH; getPdfUrl mints a 1h signed URL on demand.
- PII boundary holds: in-process under withTenant, only outbound write is the PDF
  to our own tenant-scoped storage. No LLM, no PII off-box.

### THE 40-CARD MEMORY GATE (load-bearing; Windows dev, NOT in-container)
```
cards rendered : 40 (all GENERATED)   wall-clock: 31073 ms (777 ms/card)
peak Node heap : 56.5 MB   peak Node RSS: 156.1 MB   peak Chromium: 461 MB
peak COMBINED  : 581.2 MB
vs fly.io 512MB : FAIL  (113.5%)        vs fly.io 1024MB : GREEN (56.8%)
```
**FLAGGED.** 1GB machine is comfortably GREEN (56.8%) → deploy target for PDF
render. 512MB FAILS on the Windows-dev number, but two caveats make the real
Linux figure expected-lower: Linux headless Chromium is lighter, and Win32
WorkingSet overcounts shared pages. So 512MB is undecided — MUST be re-measured
in a fly.io container. External-render fallback NOT triggered (clear GREEN at
1GB). Deferred item added: in-container re-validation + author `apps/api/Dockerfile`
with Chromium provisioning (libs + font checklist now in phase-2.md).

