### Decisions
- **Role branch via `useAuth().roles`** (not permissions — slice-5 perms are
  reference-only, PermissionsGuard is slice 9): `roles.some(r => r.key in
  {owner,admin})` = canManage. Form teachers see read-only board + View/Download;
  Build/Render/Regenerate are manager-only in the UI AND server-gated (defence in
  depth — the service already does owner/admin assertion).
- **Form-teacher scoping mirrors the gradebook**: picker filters arms to
  formTeacherArmIds; the board re-checks it client-side and the server 404s an
  out-of-scope arm anyway (assertCanReadArm). Authorization is server-truth; the
  client gate is just for clean UX.
- **Regenerate = single-card render** via the cp2 extension; optimistically flips
  that row to GENERATING locally, polling confirms. Render-all flips every row.
- **Download** opens the signed URL in a new tab (`window.open _blank
  noopener`); R2 sets Content-Disposition: attachment so it downloads.
- **Comments read-only** — slice 5 cards stay DRAFT; comment editing + the
  workflow state machine are slice 6. No textarea rendered.
- `useSearchParams` used directly in a `"use client"` page (no Suspense wrapper)
  — matches the existing `enrollments/bulk` precedent.

